text: @SchroedsBiz Hello Matt, my name is Rebecca. On behalf of FedEx, I apologize for any inconvenience or frustration that may have been caused by this matter.   If you are in the U.S. and need international assistance, please call our International Customer Service department at 1.800.GoFedEx.
@SchroedsBiz Thank you for using FedEx. We appreciate your business!
@FedExHelp I did, that’s who gave me the quote
@FedExHelp You won’t be getting any more of it, that’s for sure. What in the world is the point of the price sheet if it’s not even close to what you actually charge?

@SchroedsBiz Matt, 
I sincerely apologize for the aggravation that this has caused you.  This is not the experience we want to provide. My apologies, the U.S. Social Media team can assist with shipments inbound to the U.S.  You would need to reach back out to our international customer......

@SchroedsBiz ....service to address the issue of the rate that they gave you.  My apologies again on behalf of FedEx for the inconvenience this has caused you.  I hope that we have the opportunity to better serve you in the future.
Thank you.
